      "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<article class=\"knowledge-article\">\n<h1 id=\"title\">Python Programming Fundamentals</h1>\n<p>The concept is straightforward: python is a high-level, general-purpose programming language..</p>\n<nav class=\"table-of-contents\" aria-label=\"Table of contents\">\n<h2 id=\"contents\">Contents</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#properties\">Notable Features</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#history\">Origins and History</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#how-to\">Getting Started</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#rules\">Guidelines</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#summary\">Key Takeaways</a></li>\n</ol>\n</nav>\n<h2 id=\"properties\">Notable Features</h2>\n<p>The following features are particularly noteworthy.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Python Programming Language.</li>\n<li>Python supports multiple programming paradigms including object-oriented</li>\n<li>Python supports procedural</li>\n<li>Python supports functional programming</li>\n<li>Python has a comprehensive standard library.</li>\n<li>Python uses dynamic typing and garbage collection.</li>\n<li>Python Official Documentation.</li>\n<li>Python has several built-in data types including integers</li>\n<li>Python has floating-point numbers</li>\n<li>Python has strings</li>\n<li>Python has lists</li>\n<li>Python has dictionaries</li>\n<li>Python has tuples</li>\n<li>Python has sets</li>\n<li>Python supports list comprehensions for concise list creation.</li>\n<li>Warning: avoid using mutable objects as dictionary keys.</li>\n<li>Python Getting Started.</li>\n<li>Python virtual environments isolate project dependencies.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Together, these characteristics create a comprehensive picture.</p>\n<p>These features didn't emerge overnight. The history explains how they developed.</p>\n<h2 id=\"history\">Origins and History</h2>\n<p>The history behind this topic provides valuable context.</p>\n<p>Dating back to its origins, python was created by Guido van Rossum.. Over time, python was first released in 1991.. The historical record shows that python was designed to emphasize code readability..</p>\n<p>Understanding the history informs how we use it today.</p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to\">Getting Started</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>To install Python, download the installer from python.org.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"section-3\">Rule</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Python requires proper indentation for code blocks.</li>\n<li>Python requires version 3.8 or higher for modern features.</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"summary\" aria-label=\"Key takeaways\">\n<h2 id=\"summary\">Key Takeaways</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Python Official Documentation.</li>\n<li>Python has several built-in data types including integers</li>\n<li>Python has floating-point numbers</li>\n<li>Python has strings</li>\n<li>Python has lists</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"closing\">Python Programming Fundamentals represents a topic with 29 verified facts across 4 distinct areas of knowledge.</p>\n</section>\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"sources\">Sources</h2>\n<ol class=\"citation-list\">\n<li id=\"cite-1\"><span class=\"cite-index\">[1]</span> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Python Programming Language</a> <span class=\"cite-authority\">(encyclopedic)</span></li>\n<li id=\"cite-2\"><span class=\"cite-index\">[2]</span> <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Python Official Documentation</a> <span class=\"cite-authority\">(official)</span></li>\n<li id=\"cite-3\"><span class=\"cite-index\">[3]</span> <a href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Python Getting Started</a> <span class=\"cite-authority\">(official)</span></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"see-also\">See Also</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Definition &quot;Python is a high-level, general-purpose ...&quot; generalizes to properties</li>\n<li>Definition &quot;Python is consistently ranked among the ...&quot; generalizes to properties</li>\n<li>&quot;Python requires proper indentation for c...&quot; requires &quot;Python Programming Language.&quot;</li>\n<li>&quot;Python requires version 3.8 or higher fo...&quot; requires &quot;Python Programming Language.&quot;</li>\n<li>Definition &quot;Python lists are mutable ordered sequenc...&quot; generalizes to properties</li>\n</ul>\n</article>",
