      "content": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<article class=\"knowledge-article\">\n<h1 id=\"title\">Sql Fundamentals</h1>\n<p>To be precise, structured Query Language is used to manage and query relational databases..</p>\n<h2 id=\"properties\">Characteristics</h2>\n<p>A closer look reveals several distinctive qualities.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Structured Query Language Overview.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language stands for Structured Query Language.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language supports four main data manipulation operations: SELECT</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language supports INSERT</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language supports UPDATE</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language supports DELETE</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language databases organize data in tables with rows and columns.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language joins combine rows from two or more tables based on a related column.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language Reference Guide.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language SELECT retrieves data from one or more tables.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language WHERE clause filters rows based on specified conditions.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language GROUP BY groups rows with the same values into summary rows.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language ORDER BY sorts the result set in ascending or descending order.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language indexes improve query performance on large tables.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language primary keys uniquely identify each row in a table.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language foreign keys create referential integrity between tables.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language transactions ensure atomicity through COMMIT and ROLLBACK.</li>\n<li>Warning: avoid using SELECT * in production queries as it retrieves unnecessary columns.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Together, these characteristics create a comprehensive picture.</p>\n<p>These features didn't emerge overnight. The history explains how they developed.</p>\n<h2 id=\"history\">History</h2>\n<p>The story begins with the fact that structured Query Language was developed at IBM in the early 1970s.. From a historical perspective, structured Query Language was standardized by ANSI in 1986..</p>\n<section class=\"summary\" aria-label=\"Key takeaways\">\n<h2 id=\"summary\">Key Takeaways</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Structured Query Language Overview.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language stands for Structured Query Language.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language is used to manage and query relational databases.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language was developed at IBM in the early 1970s.</li>\n<li>Structured Query Language was standardized by ANSI in 1986.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"closing\">Sql Fundamentals represents a topic with 22 verified facts across 2 distinct areas of knowledge.</p>\n</section>\n<!-- MISSING: procedural (recommended) — How To -->\n<hr />\n<h2 id=\"sources\">Sources</h2>\n<ol class=\"citation-list\">\n<li id=\"cite-1\"><span class=\"cite-index\">[1]</span> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SQL\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">SQL Overview</a> <span class=\"cite-authority\">(encyclopedic)</span></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"see-also\">See Also</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Definition &quot;Structured Query Language is used to man...&quot; generalizes to properties</li>\n</ul>\n</article>",
